Package: recalc
Title: Recalculate Statistical Results from Reported Summary and Test Statistics
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ian", "Hussey", , "ian.hussey@unibe.ch", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8906-7559"))
  )
Description: Forensic meta-science tools that recalculate statistical results
    from the summary and test statistics reported in a paper. Reported numbers
    are rounded, and the analysis that produced them involves choices that are
    often left unstated, so a single reported result is compatible with a range
    of recalculated values rather than a single one. Given reported group means,
    standard deviations, and sample sizes -- or test statistics, correlation
    matrices, and regression coefficients -- the package recomputes p-values and
    standardised effect sizes (such as Cohen's d) across the multiverse of
    defensible choices: the rounding of each input and output, Student's versus
    Welch's t-tests, one- versus two-sided tests, and whether reported standard
    errors may have been reported as standard deviations. It returns the interval
    of recalculated values and whether the reported result falls inside it, so a
    result that cannot be reproduced under any defensible choice is distinguished
    from one that merely depends on an unstated convention. Related checks cover
    chi-squared tests, regression recovered from a correlation matrix, mediation
    analysis, coefficient alpha, and whole-versus-subgroup descriptive
    consistency.
